main event: On September 20, 1953, a civilian observer reported seeing two or more irregular shaped objects over Ashley, North Dakota.
interesting points: The objects appeared to be stationary during the observation.,The observation lasted for about 12 minutes before the objects disappeared.,No photographs or physical evidence were collected.,Military authorities investigated the sighting.,The final conclusion was that there was insufficient data to draw a definitive conclusion.
sighted object: two or more irregular shaped objects in the sky
